KADUNA – Saddened by the refusal of Kaduna Polytechnic Governing Council to allow him to participate in an interview for a rectorship position, a university lecturer Prof. Mohammed Sani Yahaya, a lecturer with the Kaduna State University, has petitioned the Hon. Minister of Education At a press conference held in Kaduna, Prof Yahaya revealed that a vacancy existed for the post of Rector in the Kaduna Polytechnic which was advertised in a newspaper on Friday 3rd Sept 2021 which he put in his application on Tuesday 12th October 2021 but was never invited for the interview scheduled for 11th and 12th 2022 by the Kaduna Polytechnic Governing Council. According to him, “The Registrar of the institution and the Secretary to the Council informed me that the invitation for an interview was not extended to me because the Governing Board has decided that a Professor is unqualified for the post of Rector and the disqualification was final and irreversible. Northern Youths Council Derides Petition  Against Senator Jibrin… Sunday Igboho Petitions FG Demands N500m For Damage Prof. Yahaya who lamented his unfair treatment said, ‘I have been illegally excluded from the interview for the post of Rector Kaduna in a gross violation of my inalienable right and out of the four candidates that rose to the rank of Chief Lecturer in Kaduna Polytechnic; three including the Acting Rector of the institution were invited for the interview, while I was deliberately excluded. “That was unfair, I believe I was also discriminated against on purpose in favour of a selected few candidates for the post of the Rector Kaduna Polytechnic while we are all equal in the sight of the law; this treatment is totally unfair. He lamented Prof. Yahaya disclosed that he has written a personal appeal for the intervention of the Executive Governor of the state, Mallam Nasiru El Rufai, The Emir of Zazzau, The Minister of Education, Minister of Justice and other stakeholders